RUNNING ALMOND AS A SIDECAR TO NGINX EXAMPLE
________________________________________________________________________________________

You can just run the script 

./start.sh

to get Almond running as a sidecar to a Nginx container.

When finsihed you can clean everything up running

./stop.sh

That´s it!

Step by step instructions described shortly below,
if you want to do steps yourself and maybe lab with the content.

*******************************************************************************************
1. Begin with creating config maps for configuration files used in the pod

	kubectl create configmap almond-plugins --from-file=plugins.conf
	kubectl create configmap almond-config --from-file=almond.conf
	kubectl create configmap almond-supervisor --from-file=supervisord-override.conf
	kubectl create configmap nginx-config --from-file=nginx.conf
	kubectl create configmap almond-nginx-scripts \
  	  --from-file=plugins/check_nginx_active.sh \
  	  --from-file=plugins/check_nginx.sh \
  	  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -

2. Apply the manifests to start the pod

	kubectl apply -f manifest.yaml
	kubectl apply -f services.yaml

3. Check that the pod is ready

   	kubectl get pods -w

4. Port forward the ports you want to use, as an example

kubectl port-forward pod/nginx-almond 8880:80 8885:8085 9890:9090 

5. Now you are ready to use the Almond API:s against the sidecar and get
   monitoring data about the applied Nginx as well as from the sidecar itself.

******************************************************************************************
